[While the serotype in the 1st article regarding Kansas is reported as being the Indiana serotype, it is likely the others mentioned in article 2 of this update are also the Indiana serotype. However, we are not told what is circulating in Nebraska.

Generally, this disease departs with killing frost, likely as insect vectors die off. At this point, I am sure all producers and regulators are ready for a frost, which is a long time from June in most parts of the affected areas. - Mod.TG

